com.ibm.avatar.algebra.datamodel

Class Text

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.avatar.algebra.datamodel.Text

  • public class Text
extends Object
    Wrapper for raw document text that provides the Span API. This API allows operators to run directly on top of the document text as if it were a span.

        public Pair<String,String> getViewAndColumnName()
        Returns:
        If this Text object has been attached to a tuple of a view, the name of the view and the column within the view containing this Text object. If the object is associated with more than one tuple (or multiple fields within the same tuple), the first assignment will set this field and remaining assignments will leave this field alone.Null if this Text object has not been associated with any view.

      • translateOffset

        public int translateOffset(int offset)
        If this text was derived from another one, translate the indicated offset of the current string into the corresponding offset of the original string. For example, the first character of the current string may be the fifth character of the original string, so this would translate 1 to 5.

        The offset table maps the offset in the derived text to the offset in the original text.

        Example:
        Original text: "A /* comment */short"
        Derived text (with comments stripped): "A short"
        Offset table = {0, 1, 15, 16, 17, 18, 19}. 

         
        
 
        
 offset in derived text
 offset in original text
 character at the offset in both texts
 
        
 
         ix offsetTable (ix)  
        
 
 
        0 0  A
        
 
        1 1  ' ' (space)
        
 
        2 15 s
        
 
        3 16 h
        
 
        4 17 o
        
 
        5 18 r
        
 
        6 19 t
        Parameters:
        offset - offset of current string
        Returns:
        corresponding offset of original string

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()
        Generate hash code for Text object consistent with the object relations.

        If the text object is not derived, use the string hash code.

        If the text object is derived, use the combination of its string hash code as well as the hash code of the source, and the first element of mapping table.

        Overrides:
        hashCode in class Object

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(SpanText other)
        Compare two Text objects, according to the following list of rules. These rules are examined in the given order, and first unequal result is returned.
        • A null object is ordered lower than other objects.
        • The objects are compared by the lexical order of their string values.
        • If neither of the objects are derived, they compare equal.
        • If only one of the objects is derived, it is ordered higher than the other.
        • The objects are compared by the lexical order of their source string values
        • The objects are compared by the sorting order of the mapping tables, which is guaranteed to be stable and compatible with equality, but the actual order is internal and should not be relied upon.
        Parameters:
        other - the text to be compared against the current text
        Returns:
        1 if the current text sorts higher than the input text, -1 if the input text sorts higher than the current text, 0 if they are equal
